
This directory has code to allow piglet to produce gerbers for PCB fabrication.

The basic idea is to draw your layers directly using the "layers" file for each
of the features of your pcb: top,bottom, drill holes, etc.  The layer definitions
in the layers file are arbitrary and you can change them.  However the rest of the 
scripts in this directory assume that they are used as is.

FILES:

gbs     ; the gerber converter script.  Edit this file to put the name of
        ; your project in the definition for $PIGTOP.  When you run this program
        ; it will run piglet in the background, plot all the files to a combined
        ; gerber output, split the file into individual gerbers and create a zip
        ; file for sending to the PCB shop.  Towards the bottom of the file, you'll
        ; need to comment out or uncomment the layers that you want to be included

g2loc   ; takes a split out gerber files for the component layers and outputs
        ; coordinates for pick and place

dolocs  ; calls g2loc for top and bottom component layers to produce a combined
        ; pick and place file

g2drill ; processes the drill layers an produces a gerber drill file.  Drill hits
        ; are made by including a square rectangle in the design on every hole.  The
        ; center of the square is the drill location and the width is the drill diameter

layers      ; a list of layers and their meanings 

MENUDATA_V  ; a custom menu for PCB design

NOTEDATA.F  ; some appropriate fonts

PROCDATA.P  ; a process file to make useful fill and colors consistent with the layers file

README      ; an example README to include to the PCB fab shop.  Edit this file to match
            ; your design and it will be included in the output zip file when you run gbs
